    "plan_content": "## Plan Summary\n\n**Root cause:** Off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts` — the `processItems` loop uses `i < items.length - 1`, which stops one index too early, skipping the last element entirely.\n\n**The fix:** Remove `- 1` from the loop condition on line 7:\n\n```typescript\n// Before (buggy)\nfor (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {\n\n// After (fixed)\nfor (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {\n```\n\n**Impact:** 3 of 6 tests currently fail (`should process all items`, `should handle a single item`, `should handle two items`). All will pass after this single-character fix.\n\n**Only file to change:** `src/utils.ts`",
